    'index' => 'ee519',
    'body' => 'Some people (me among them) note that Traveller reactors seem to be
able to fuse pure H1, rather than the deuterium or tritium that more
realistic reactors require. From this I infer that Traveller reactors contain
a
nuclear damper running in reverse, as it were, to increase the fusion
probabilities for H+H=>D (note: this requires tweaking the electroweak
force too, but we\'ll ignore that.)

In that case, the reactors own damper might protect it from external
interference
at anything but the shortest ranges.

Bruce
