  {
    'body' => 'At 22:45 -0500 20/11/99, "Josh W. Spencer" <macmanjws@earthlink.net> wrote:

>OK, can you fill me in then on this Roger <spit> Sanger character? When
>did he purchase the DGP materials and why is he in dispute with Marc Miller?

Roger bought DGP off Joe Fugate (IIRC) who did a lot of the work for 
GDWs\' MT publications in addition to the DGP material. This happened 
after DGP withdrew from the Traveller market when TNE was published.

At this present moment, several list members are owed money by DGP 
for material printed and sold years ago. Roger has started many 
projects for RPGs since he bought DGP, none of which have come to 
fruition.

His dispute with MM relates to the ownership of the DGP material. 
Although RS owns the copyright of the text for the DGP material he 
cannot publish without MM\'s permission. RS wants a lot of money for 
the DGP material. As a result, it is legally dubious to use DGP 
material as a basis for current Traveller material and both T4 and GT 
avoided reusing it by working around it. As a result, some of the 
best Traveller material is being overwritten and is condemned to 
being rare collector\'s items.

Other people who were on the list earlier than me may have a better 
description, as mine is not first hand, only the story as I have been 
told.

Dom

