> You appear to be suffering from a common misconception. It\'s not
> *possible* to keep things like nukes "secret" if they *ever* get used,
> and it\'s fairly unlikely even if they *don\'t* get used.

Yes, I know... but:

The way I interpret Vargr makes it... ahem... difficult for them to
research a thing like that. IMTU, they mostly steal things that other
people have. They know how to build things like slugthrowers, simple
spaceships and such, but advanced technology (hand-held laser weapons,
jumpdrives etc) they have to steal, purchase, or get from the Zho\'s (who
secretly sponsor them). Yes, this means that occassional Vargr Corsairs
pack some stolen nukes, but not on a large scale.

The Vargr are simply far too impatient to research anything complicated.
They have more enthusiasm than actual scientific skills. This got them
into space using large rockets (and blowing several of them into tiny
bits before that). A Vargr researching nukes would think something along
the lines of:

"OK... so this thing can explode. I\'ll test it in the back yard and see
how much. Calculating the stuff takes too much time."

BOOM!

