    'month' => '11',
    'topic' => ' Weapons of mass destruction',
    'body' => 'At 12:37 AM 11/22/1999 +0100, you wrote:

>The way I interpret Vargr makes it... ahem... difficult for them to
>research a thing like that. IMTU, they mostly steal things that other
>people have. They know how to build things like slugthrowers, simple
>spaceships and such, but advanced technology (hand-held laser weapons,
>jumpdrives etc) they have to steal, purchase, or get from the Zho\'s (who
>secretly sponsor them). Yes, this means that occassional Vargr Corsairs
>pack some stolen nukes, but not on a large scale.

The Vargr developed jump drive, and Lair has a higher TL that the Zhondani.
 As I recall from AM3, the Vargr found the Zhos, not the other way around.

Quite the opposite, I feel the Vargr mind set would encourage scientific
development.  Why?  Charisma.  Vargr are intelligent creatures, and the
Vargr who developed the Theory of Relativity would be the Alpha of Vargr
physicists.

It\'s tempting to see the Vargr as a wild howling pack of dogs.  Indeed,
that the impression the give much of the time.  But to ignore that they
inhabit an area of space equal if not larger than the Imperium and have
inhabited that area since before the First Imperium came along does them a
disservice.

Charisma is a difficult thing to get a handle on.  To be blunt, probably
the closet thing we can use as a comparison is lust.  Humans are
pre-programmed to react to certain indicators given off by the opposite
gender (same gender if you are gay-- and the odd thing is that they aren\'t
the same one that an opposite sex partner would respond to) with the
physical urge to mate.  Take away the higher brain functions, and human
males would do nothing but attempt to mate constantly.  (I\'m sure some of
the women on list would say that that\'s true even with the higher functions
in place :P)

But we can control that urge, for the most part.  We might have a physical
reaction, but we can understand that making a pass at the cop who is
writing you a ticket for 75 in a school zone is a Bad Idea.  The same for
charisma in a Vargr.  That new guy may be impressive as all hell, but
raiding Rhylanor in a single Corsair is suicide!  There will always be
Vargr who let their emotions guide them, just as there will be humans who
do the same.

Geez, start writing a reply and end up looking like the Vargr
Anti-Defemation League...
