option 1: Move the mine to the miners. In order to reduce shipping delay of raw
materials to refineries, rich asteroids can be put into a low thrust intercept
to the location of said refineries. While they could take months or years, well
timed boosts could arrange an asteroid every other month.

option 2: Cheap transport. In a Jerry Pournelle book (Leonard will know which
one, I cant remember of hand), the miners hollowed out a rich nickel/iron
asteroid, filled it up with small amounts of VERY rich and rare alloys, as wll
as hold and silver, and blasted it to earth with an orion drive.

