    If you\'re dropping troops to the surface to grab what is, in all
likelihood,
an already well-defended target, such as a starport or other "high value
target", why wouldn\'t you make that, or one of those, your main beachhead?
If you\'re talking "hit and get" raids, yeah, but I got the impression that
you
were talking seize and _hold_ the starport.  Troops already on the ground
would make suppression of local air-defense (or their analogue) possible
as well as being able to designate/clear landing zones as well as giving
the main force, hopefully, a relatively fire-free zone to muster in.
    I could be wrong, but it read to me as if you were saying that the
"initial raids" and "pathfinder landing" were two different and completely
seperate stages.  It would seem to me to be better to combine them.
If nothing else, this forces the defender to decide what is a feint, what is
a raid, and what is the legitimate main force landing (re: Hitler, Normandy,
and Pas-de-Calais).
                                                            Lyle
