> troops in oder to capture
> the planet?  Together in armored shuttles (I think
> this is a bad idea
> myself) or like in Starship Troopers, where they
> drop individually
> \'halo-style\'?
>
J-Man, each has their advantages and disadvantages.
Shuttles make targets, big and obvious, but
individuals are smaller targets, and hopefully one
blast doesn\'t take out a whole company. However the
old problem with paradrops is that the unit gets
broken up. If you\'ve trained with Sgt Slaughter,
Corporal Jim-Bob and your best friend Cyril every day
for the past two years in the "Glorious Gonzo
Company", and suddenly down on the ground you\'re with
a bunch of bozos you don\'t know, in the "Confused
Klutz Company", well, you\'re just not going to fight
as well. In military strategy when the enmey mixes you
all up in a mass of confusion, nobody knowing who\'s in
charge, they call that "disruption," and it\'s a chief
aim of the enemy, who will happily drive armour into
your flanks to finish you off. When you do it to
yourself, it\'s not called "disruption", it\'s called "a
successful paradrop."

I\'d go for the armoured cars, myself. Unless unit
cohesion ain\'t important to you, which I suppose it
isn\'t if you have trained beserker fanatics who don\'t
need back-up or organisation.... "I only need to know
one thing... where the bugs are... blood blood blood!"

