> I just pictured an Impy Marine being launched in full BD at some planet
> doing roughly 22,000 miles per hour. I know, I know, he would burn up on
> entry into the atmosphere but the thought was there none the less. Huummmm,
> if you could cool him down, I wonder just how big a crater he would make?

Well, 22,000 mph is about 6 miles/sec. or about 9.8 km/sec. At *3*
km/sec the impact energy is equivalent to an equal mass of TNT going
off. Energy goes up as the square of the velocity. 

So my figures say he goes off like 11 times his mass in TNT. Assume 250
kilos for trooper and suit, and you get the equivalent of an old time
"block buster" bomb (actually about 2.6 tons of TNT)

