Niven style "stasis fields" would be *great* for drops. Form up a
company (or whatever) in BD, slap a stasis fiels around them, and throw
them at the target, with the field set to drop just after impact. The
field drops and they bounce out of the still glowing crater....

Oddly, they aren\'t all that great for defensive use. You can\'t *do*
anything while inside them, since a second inside is a few million
years outside. And you can\'t shoot out of them either. Nor do they
"hide" that well. 

Turn one on as a "last resort" and when it goes down, you\'ll either be
surrounded by enemy weapons, ready to be set off, or if you *really*
pissed them off, the weapons *will* go off as soon as the field goes.
