    'body' => '> One good question deserves another, under the same
> set of circumstances how
> differentiated do you think Vargr will have become? 
>witness the
> wide variance in modern
> canine breeds.  

In modern canine breeds, there are families rather
than species. Eg the modern "sausage dog" came from
16th centruy England, when a breeder dred a
long-bodied dog with another, got their children to
mate with each-other, selected the longest-bodied of
_their_ children, and so on. Essentially it\'s a case
of breeding _in_ the recessive genes. You could do
exactly the same with humans if you wanted to, and
were patient. For example, you could create a race of
"hobbits" by breeding one midget with another, and
making their children mate with each-other, and so on.
Canine "breeds" are very simply inbred families.
(anybody seen the X-Files episode, "home"? icky!) If
you could make Michael Jordan mate with the head of
the Russian women\'s basketball team, you could make a
race of "giants", and so on.

So I\'d say the Vargr would probably just be mongrels,
really. I\'m sure that with language and higher
intelligence they would have developed the same incest taboo.

