>were talking seize and _hold_ the starport.  

Way bother grabbing the starport at all? If commercial starships can land
at a type X starport (AKA a big empty field) than a combat lander should be
able to. 

So, for a planetary assault you could drop a brigade or two in a deserted
spot. They grab a large enough area for your combat engineers or seabees to
build a new starport. The new starport lets you land troops in a secure
area while the people on the planet are busy re-routing their troops to an
area they were not prepared to defend. If you are not willing to bombard
high value targets, well, the local troops will be coming to you so you can
hit them in a low value area.

And if the locals don\'t come out to play? Grap the rest of the planet and
starve them out. (What tech level does weather control become practical?)

Granted, this won\'t work with a world with a high enough pop. A world with
a population greater than maybe 7 or so, you will probably end up having to
hit at least  some of the population centers hard. This might start out
with EMP bursts and escalate (clean airbursts to burn soft targets) if the
locals didn\'t surrender.

And a final thought. The Imperium is made up of 11,000 worlds. Burning one
world every few decades might be a cost effective measure if it makes other
worlds think twice about leaving.

