infeasible are also less than relevant to my original comments. The point is
that even with the capability for extremely high levels of violence, most
(notice the use of this word, in case anyone decides to give a list of
counterexamples) groups agree to a set of conventions which limit the impact
of the fighting.

Rambling on:

Note that even under the current law of land warfare, you are entitled to
reprisals if your enemy violates the conventions. Considering the number of
violations by the Iraqis in the Gulf War, think about the possible *real*
reason for some events in the war.

