    'body' => 'I wrote:
>>>
IMHO, the best riot control weapon is something with no medical side
effects, able to be targeted effectively, and has minimal secondary
effects.  Watar canons seem to fit the bill. Water casues no alergic
reactions, the delivery will at most cause abrasions and blunt trauma
(on hitting the ground  or obsticals) and can be aimed to avoid
children and elderly (who have a higher chance of sustainig more
serious injury with the secondary effects.
<<<

Leonard wrote
>>>
You\'ve never seen what a regular fire hose can do, have you? And you\'ve
*definitely* never seen what a water cannon can.

At the speeds and pressures involved, the *water* can break bones. You
don\'t have to be thrown against anything.
<<<

I reply:

Selective quoting can be a bitch. If you read the previous paragraph I stated
that non leathal weapons aren\'t. I meant that no matter what is used, fatalities
*will* occur. No Ifs, no buts.


Leonard again:
>>>
There are pictures available of the time the authorities used "mere"
firehoses on civil rights demonstrators in the South. And you can see
the water stream "pick up" and "throw" people 10 and 20 feet. Anything
pushing hard enough to do *that* and less than a foot across can and
will produce blunt trauma all by itself.
<<<

I reply:

A knoted string will kill in the wrong hands. Any feasable riot control weapon
requires a brain to use. If you are going to use high preasure water at knife
fighting ranges, then you MUST expect casulties. It was one of the strong points
mentioned in the Non Lethal Weapons show on Discovery.

Water IF USED CORRECTLY is:

1. Non irratant. It will not cause fits and alogegnic reations. It is non
poisonous. It cannot cause toxic shock. If it does puncture the skin it can not
cause any secondary effects (apart from the trauma itself).

2. Aimable. Yes you can aim at heads. But aiming at the torso or legs is more
effective and harder to avoid.

3. Cheap. In non deasert enviroments, water is cheap, and in a pinch can be made
by burning hydrogen. Any starship can be used as a riot vehicle in a pinch (and
may be a feature on some ships!).


Leonard again
>>>
As for water cannon, there are cases on record (from repressive
regimes) where they were used and *cut people in half*. Those things
can punch holes in concrete blocks or some frame buildings. Using them
on people is *not* remotely "without medical side effects".
<<<

Again, we are talking about the system, not the people using it. If you want to
use it to kill, there are better ways of doing it. If you using excessive force
to crush a riot, why use water? Plasma guns and Fusion guns haver better ranges,
better blowthrough (I got 3 gollywogs with 1 shot!) and better fear causing
atributes (people wont generally assult a plasma gun enplacement no matter
what). I can suppress a riot with knotted sting, and kill people with it (and
has been historically used , it\'s called a whip).

<scenerio : Me as riot suppressor commander>

Do I have the will to use lethal force and live with the consequences?

No.

If called to suppress a riot with water, would I do it? Yes.

Why?

Because I know if I keep control of the situation, I can minimalise the
causualties. I want to cause fear and loathing in the rioters, not martyrs for
the cause. If I loose control of my troops, no mater what they are armed with
(chopsticks, canes, whips, SMG\'s, black puddings) they can and will kill. (Ask
the East Timorese).

</scenerio>

I would fear a uncontrolled force armed with silly putty , or a force willing to
use leathal force more than I would a profesional force with a water cannon.

And history shows that sooner or later, a government that resorts to leathal
force against its own will fall.

Darryl
