>...
>>>Oh, but wait, doesn\'t the Imperium have laws against multiworld polities?
>>
>>Doubtful, since each sector has a government and a fleet (CT: HG), as does
>>almost every subsector (ibid), plus there are imperial worlds that "own"
>>other worlds...
>
>  But aren\'t the lower level fleets merely portions of the Imperium with
>a divergent organization? They don\'t actually serve a separate foreign
>policy - although as you indicate a potential difference of opinions on
>internal issue is the big question.
>
Well, since it is stated in HG that they are separate fleets, and I\'ve seen
references to "Local" fleets in at least two adventures, I think that
they\'re probably NOT the same things... so Basically, since CT and MT
assume a semi-feudal late 3I, I took that to mean their own governance,
taxation, and fleets. So IMTU, the Imperial Navy has it\'s Numbered and
Sector Fleets. The Sector Duke has his "Reserve Fleets". The Subsector
Dukes have their "Police Fleets", which match the numbered reserve fleets
answerable to the Sector duke, at least in number (although seldom by
tyupes or numbers of hulls), and any world which can afford it has at least
a few SDB\'s or Type-T\'s...

So, in any given world, you have the local Government\'s Fleet, a portion of
the Subsector Fleet, the possibility of a portion of the Sector Duke\'s
Numbered Reserve Fleet, and a possibility of a portion of the Imperial
Numbered Fleet for that subsector, plus a possibility for a portion of the
Sector Dukes Named Reserve Fleet, and a possibility of a portion of the
Imperial Named Fleet. And, if part of some sub-subsector polity, the
Count\'s Fleets might show, too!

Then again, IMTU, the Imperial Government levies a 1% stock levy per
issuance for all off-planet buisinesses, for each of the following:
Subsector Duke of Homeworld, Sector Duke of Each Sector operated in, Each
Archduke whose domains are operated in, and 1% more to the Emperor (who is
also Archduke of Sylea, thus getting 2%). I make it part of the Office,
rather than the Fief. Plus, Most Subsectors and sectors IMTU charge between
0.1% and 1.5% GPP taxes, too.


