>>combatants and non-combatants will most likely be blurred, and the
>>distinction between civilian and war production will most certainly be
>>blurred?
>
>Sounds just like the invasion of Terra during the Solomani Rim War.


You\'ve made my point for me. In this case, only the avatar of destruction is
being changed, not the fact that the destruction occurs. From the point of
view of the Imperium, the use of big rocks is much cheaper than a marine
invasion, so why is it that folks claim that such scenarios will be "rare"?
