Heh. I have a semi-funny story relating to that... A 
classmate of mine and I went to a local ham enthusiasts\'
club one night (we were both in computer engineering at the
time in university). There were a couple of guys from Bell
giving a presentation on how they installed fiber lines.
They had one of these cool boxes with multiple camera/microscope
and a tiny little arc welder that made splicing fiber seem 
pretty damn easy (having had to do it by hand in a lab, let
me tell you that butting up two pieces of fiber, half the
diameter of a human hair, is not easy).

After hearing about all the wonderful properties of fiber
versus copper one of the HAMs, totally serious, stood up
and said how great fiber would be to run from his power 
amplifer to his antenna, to eliminate all the cross-talk and 
noise he was always getting.

Now, on the other hand, in all fairness, I can barely work
