more often in religious conflicts that nationalist or ideological
conflicts.  Whilst the two \'World Wars\' had many documented cases of
atrocities, I suspect that in proportion to the numbers of combatants
involved many of the smaller conflicts in history founded in religion were
far nastier. </Dave>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         !
