    'month' => '11',
    'topic' => ' dampers and reactors',
    'body' => 'In mail you write:

> In the Starship Operators guide it did say that fusion reactors had a
> deuterium tank which was used for crash starting the reactor. Could not the
> fuel purification system include items to seperate deuterium and possibly
> tritium to help initiate the fusion reaction?

It\'s a nice idea, but it\'s about as practical as trying to start a big
lump of anthracite (hard coal) on fire with a match.

"Protium" (H1) requires *much* higher temperatures and pressures than
deuterium or D-T mixtures. As I recall we are talking *orders of
magnitude* higher (10 to 100 times).

On the other hand, there are reactor designs being looked at that
*don\'t* require high temp and high pressure. But they tend to require
rather *large* reactors.

