I\'m not quite familiar enough to deal with the American revolution, so I
will just deal with the French case.

Basically, the peasants provided the bulk of the force behind the
revolution, along with the urban masses, the sans-culottes.  This is for
the good and simple reason that the peasants were the _overwhelming_
majority of the French population.

"Elite" revolts that face opposition need mass support, or they will fail.

