>>>Way bother grabbing the starport at all? If commercial starships can land
>>>at a type X starport (AKA a big empty field) than a combat lander should be
>>>able to. 

Sure. *Some* starships can land at type X ports. They then have to load
or unload *by hand*, or pretty close to it. What a decent port could
unload in an hour might take them all day. 

This is the same reason that the Allies made a point of capturing a
relatively intact seaport shortly after D-Day. You *can* get troops and
supplies ashore via landing craft. But it takes specialized vehicles,
and takes a lot of time. 

Ports also have fueling facilities, and are tied into the local
transportation net. that last won\'t be *quite* as important in a CG
using civilization, but I bet there\'s still stuff better handled by
road or some sort of "subway" or even pipeline. 

> Which is why you don\'t want to launch an all out planetary assault on it.
> You want the starport intact for after the war, so you pull the defending
> forces away from the port before engaging them.

Just keep in mind that the *other* side wants that port intact too.
You\'ll mostly see major facilities being destroyed when the enemy is
fighting on territory that they took away from someone else. 

Otherwise it\'s a good sign that they consider the situation hopeless
and have decided that the only thing left to do is destroy things to
keep you from using them. 

