    'from' => 'Kyle Schuant kyle3054@yahoo.com',
    'body' => 'What the conventions and protocols actually say:

"The High Contracting Parties undertake to respect and
to ensure respect for the present Convention in all
circumstances." 

"...Although one of the Powers in conflict may not be
a party to the present Convention, the Powers who are
parties thereto shall remain bound by it in their
mutual relations...." (ie, you\'ve got to follow the
rules even if the enemy doesn\'t, if you have already
agreed to the rules, eg, Allies didn\'t get to murder
Japs in camps just because the Japs hadn\'t signed the
Conventions)

Also, you can\'t order reprisals against: medical
personnel, prisoners of war, the wounded and sick,
chaplains, or the civilian population. That\'s
everybody except the boys fighting, and probably they
don\'t care whether your shooting them is an attack or
"reprisal"; the bullet stings your bum just the same!

Those who can wade through the legalese I recommend to
the following site for links to the full texts of the
conventions (war crimes down the bottom of the
screen):
http://www.hri.ca/uninfo/treaties/

You\'ll note, by these standards, every party to every
conflict we can think have war criminals...


