This is a good place to point out that cultural differences can get you
in *real* trouble with this sort of thing. As an extreme example, check
out L.E. Modesitt\'s "Adiamante". 

A culture that considers "if you do that, we\'ll do this" to be a form
of aggression. Likewise for displays of force. All they can do is try
to set up situations where if their "visitors" can actually stop and
*think through* the implications of things they are seeing, they might
figure out that they\'ll be in big trouble if they start anything.

And, naturally, part of the problem is that even when they let the
"vistors" read a copy of the "rules" they live by (or the basic
principles behind them) the visitors reaction is "They can\'t *really*
mean that".

