Certainly not. A dinosaur-killer rock would probably accomplish the feat
you desired (unless you *really* wanted to remove the whole thing in
order to get a better view or something).

> On a typical Earthlike world with a liquid metallic core would not
> removing a sizable chunk of the mantle result in a sudden reduction of
> pressure on the core, the core then exploding outward thus completing
> the planets destruction?

The liquid mass would travel upwards and solidify. This is what happens
constantly when the tectonic plates are moving away from each other.
Thankfully, this doesn\'t destroy the Earth :-)

