OK - there are presently 7 101 Books so you probably have them all.

The Long Way Home is now out of print, as is first edition 101 
Cargos(*) and first edition copies of the Traveller Bibliography.

(*) The difference is that a new set of cargos were generated as Jo 
Grant\'s originals were grabbed for JTAS by IG. SJG have always had 
the second edition of this.

But, \'SpaceDogs\' and \'The Khiidkar Incident\' are both out now. These 
are 101 sized (ie LBB size) adventures with stats for GT and T4 and 
notes on using the system with all Traveller editions. SJG will 
probably have them in for Christmas. In the mean time, Leisure Games 
in London have copies and Esdevium (big UK games supplier) probably 
will too (if not now, pretty soon). FWIW these adventures were 
released following the TMLs cries for adventures in the LBB style. If 
they sell more, we have more to release; if not, well, we tried to 
give people what they asked for!

We\'re hoping to have the following out for Christmas:
- ----

At Close Quarters - Doug Berry\'s detailed combat rules for Traveller, 
famous for Penguins.

101 Patrons - over a hundred patrons for Traveller, including 
material by Andy Slack (the 36 dramatic situations) and Thad Coons 
(World Seeds as originally seen on the TML). This will be almost a 
sequel to 101 Plots but bigger, harder (science) and better (IMO but 
I edited and wrote a chunk of it).

The Traveller Bibliography 2nd Edition - Timothy Collinson\'s 
excellent guide to all things Traveller.

Obviously, the release dates of this will be as soon as we can get 
them out - we all work for a living (and sadly not in RPGs) and have 
to fit in BITS work around real life. UK release usually predates US 
release as SJG have to see the BITS book before they say yes and 
order it.

