Well Tim, you\'ve opened a can o\' worms here! ;^)

You\'ll surely here as many different answers as there are people on the TML!
Here\'s mine.

I really believe that if your playing by email then , if your running a game
yourself, I\'d concider buying the reprints of the CT version that Marc has
coming out, ot GURPS:Traveller, since both of these offer (or will offer in
the immediate future) large, and reasonably complete data bases to work
from.

Most email games are combines of several versions, but since all but G:T and
TNE are basically updates of Classic Traveller, the reprints would be a good
start. So if your planing to be a player in someone elses game, I\'d start
there then let your GM guide you if more specific information is required.

Saying all this you might think I\'m a CT fan, but really, since I got back
into the game a few years ago, I\'ve been building a collection of
MegaTraveller stuff. For the most part I find that MT took the better parts
of CT and added some real time and effort saving features (task system,
integrated large scale combat, etc.), T4, dispite it\'s best efforts never
reached this stage of integration, in my opinion. G:T, since the base system
is so large, has these opertunities as well, however GURPS, as I\'ve learned
from several gamse I\'ve run, can get complicated, and IMHO doesn\'t lend well
to PEM (too many die rolls involved in combat, etc.). MT has the draw back
of being mostly expensive and hard to find.

Humm, Hope some of this helps,

Mike
