    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

Chris suggests that the big 3I would use nasty weapons on dissenting worlds:
>At some point, if you\'re the Imperium, and you\'re as hardnosed as is claimed
>in canon, you\'re going to have to deal with the pontentiality of hitting
>civilian populations to make it known that you\'re not going to tolerate such
>slacking.

My take is that since the Pacification Campaigns, especially the abortive
Antarean Campaign, the Imperium has realised that this sort of thing doesn\'t
work that well. It\'s not good economics, for one thing.

Since the Alkhalikoi dynasty has been in power, all the Imperium does is
increase diplomatic pressure, up to and including Red Zoning the system (part of
which included destroying the world\'s starships and ship building facilities, if
any). This quarantines the world from interstellar trade, which Far Trader
suggests is necessary for the world to survive and rise in TL. Naturally, it
works better on some worlds than others - Ag worlds can hold out better than
Vacc worlds, for example. Some worlds even prefer not to rise in TL - oh well,
they\'re not going to produce a lot of tax, in any event.

The Imperium takes the long view, that the world will, sooner or later, decide
to rejoin and petition for a removal of the interdiction.

This policy works for the odd one or two worlds that try it. A concerted effort
to leave the Imperium by a group of worlds hasn\'t occurred yet - at least, not
until the Rebellion... ;-)

...then the policy changes to the Black War scenario, which is (really) what you
have all already suggested would be the final outcome...
