    'body' => '>Finally, I never bought the business of "we have ways
>of making you pay." How does a bank foreclose on a
>mortgage if the residence has Jump-3? And I don\'t want
>to hear about transponders and "late payment messages
>stopping the engine." If an engineer put it there,
>another engineer can remove it!

IMTU, it\'s fairly simple: Banks won\'t finance J5 or J6 ships. Period. J4\'s
will only be financed when there is a viable collateral OTHER THAN THE SHIP.

J3 ships require a good buisiness plan, and while anything put in can be
removed or replaced, if you can\'t outrun the news, you\'d better keep the
payments in line. Most of the "Pirates" (by cgen career) are actually skip
tracers most of the time, starmercs when needed, and privateers when
available. The banks tend to send J-4 messages when a ship makes it\'s
payments, to all payment acceptance stations within 2 months hard travel
from point of payment. Most worlds maintain lists of ships in the area; if
a ship is more than two months out by local computations, they prepare a
skip alert... Not that they announce the ship has skipped, but that customs
needs to check for papers (if the law level allows) or the bank hires a
skip tracer to "take a look"; most (almost all) ship financing allows the
banks\' local agent to inspect or authorize inspection by their deputy as
"part owner". If the agent finds proof of payment, fine, he\'s got to leave.
Otherwise, including if the crew refuses access to the papers and/or ship
after seeing appropriate credentials, the agent may reposess the ship "On
suspicion". I only did this to a PC group once... it ended the campaign
(They wound up confined to an imperial prison world, since the note holder
was the Imperial Government, and the "Tracer" was an IMOJ field agent...
whom they shot.)

Since I use the "pirates" as skip tracers, it gives reason for banks to
subsidize or even finance pirate vessels... field authorizations! And a
letter or Marque and Reprisal, with clauses allowing inspection of records
of vessels financed by a given bank, or government, and siezure if not able
to prove current payments. That, and the pirates keeping tabs on skip
reports.

