    'body' => 'Howdy folks.  I\'ve got here a new can \'o worms, and I want to
open it up.  It concerns the potential difference between political
and cultural boundaries, sort of.

Ask a Traveller player where the Spinward Marches is, and show
her a map, and most likely she can figure it out if she doesn\'t already
know.

Fine.  Now ask a native of the Aramis subsector (or District 268, or
Five Sisters) where the Spinward Marches is, and he might say his
region isn\'t really "the same as" the rest of the Marches.  In short, a
border area might claim a bit of individuality that separates it from the
sector\'s core.

Frontier gives way to wilderness on one side and civilization on the
other... and location has an effect on its inhabitants.

So then, an exercise to the reader would be to take a close look at
the Spinward Marches and pick out the areas that, quite frankly,
don\'t really fit the mold... if there even is a mold for this sector.
Where do their cultural ties rest?

Now, I wouldn\'t suggest this kind of exercise for, say, Deneb,
because they\'ve only got one Imperial border.  But the Marches
might have clusters that prefer Deneb worlds, or might be solid
Marches supporters, or might be only marginal.

What do you think?

This is only an exercise.  If it doesn\'t go anywhere, that\'s fine.

- -Rob
