11000 stars at a concentration of 1 per 2 cubic parsecs would only be a
distance of 17 parsecs from the core to the edge.  Even allowing for
non-spherical shapes and lower stellar densities I can\'t imagine a radius of
more than maybe 30 parsecs.  I think the galactic disk is 1000-1500 parsecs
thick in the region of the sun.  The galaxy is a big place.

Given the rather huge size of the galaxy, is there anything else out there?
For starters, the Zhodani sent expeditions most of the way to the galactic
core.  Did they really discover no other major powers?

Mark.
