Basically, if you wanted to have more cheap, tramp starships, what you\'d need to do is recognize that 100 dT is BIG, and that the electronics for starships are pretty outlandish as well.  An age of sail tramp steamer would probably be more like 10-20 dT, and pretty cheaply made as well.  It isn\'t surprising that these enormous, extremely capable ships (your average free trader is probably 30-40 meters long) are also expensive.

