    'body' => 'Kyle writes: 

perhaps we could adjust the definition of
a superpower to, "without another power\'s
co-operation, providing that there is no widesporead
opposition." That is, if you are a superpower, "those
who not against us are with us." To be truly neutral
and "non-interventionist" means to make the strong
stronger, the weak weaker. 
I can\'t imagine any nation ever being powerful enough
that its enemies and rivals, united, couldn\'t defeat
it. But just as one bully may scare twety classmates
who, together, could easily beat him up... who wants
to be the first to step forward and say, "hey, bully!
cut that out!" And if the bully is a benevolent ruler,
only demanding you let him sell you Coca-Cola and
episodes of "Friends," well, you might put up with
him...   

KA Schuant
     
