> aeroliens (sp?) and such. It\'s assumed you\'re not
> intersted in its wingless weight, since all that
> weight, whatever it is, will be, um, "dead" weight."

You are confusing "streamlining" and "airframe". Most *cars* are
streamlined. This means that air folows over them smoothly, and in a
manner calculated to not destabilize the vehicle (ie the car doesn\'t
have a stron tendency to turn into the wind, but a strong gust will
still push it sideways). 

Airframe is where you start worrying about stuff like generating lift
and major aerodynamic control surfaces. 

