above a certain size, they\'d drop an ortillery round on it. 

I think there were regular drops of vitamin mineral supplements, and
minimal medical supplies, too. For all the goos a plastic crate and a
parachute did the prisoners as "raw materials".

They managed to escape. And no, I don\'t remember how.

Also, check out Jack Vance\'s "the Blue World" for an example of how to
produce metals on a planet with no workable deposits. The basic idea is
that given a strong heat source, and carbon to act as a reducing agent,
things like *blood* can be a metal source. Many plants and animals
selectively concentrate various metals.

