The problem there is actually multiple, interlocking problems. First,
the Arabs are understandably reluctant to set the precedent of allowing
outsider removal of a (theoretically) Arab, Moslem leader.

Second, it\'s not politically feasible for us to just take over. Which
leads to the third problem. If we eliminate Saddam, who replaces him?
There\'s *no* credible opposition faction left. He saw to that via
extermination. So we\'d get either someone who is much the same, or we\'d
get a weak leader. And if we got a weak leader, Iran would invade (and
*win*) in a heartbeat. 

