I would allow any character who receives a ship as a mustering-out
benefit (and also has all prerequisite skills) an automatic Master\'s
ticket for the appropriate class of vessel.  Further, I would allow a
ship owner or primary operator to receive a provisional Master\'s ticket
(regardless of skills), which would allow shipment of non-hazardous
cargo (no passengers) within certain specified shipping lanes.  Routine
passenger traffic would require a Master\'s 4th Class or better ticket,
although one-shot passages would not fall under this category.  (As an
analogy, if I pick up a hitch-hiker, I don\'t need a special license,
even if the passenger pays me gas money.  OTOH, I would need a
chauffeur\'s license to drive a bus or taxicab.)

Naval officers with combat commands (if generated using High Guard)
would automatically carry Master\'s tickets based on their rank at the
time of command:  O3 or less, Master 5th class; O4-O5, Master 3d class;
O6+, Master 1st class.  Note that naval officers with combat commands do
_not_ have to possess all (or any) required skills to obtain the ticket
appropriate to their rank; commanding a ship in combat is considered
prima facie evidence of ability to command a vessel.  Naval officers
without combat commands at the desired level must possess all required
skills for a given ticket to receive that ticket; in such a case,
receipt of the ticket is automatic (this could indicate a peacetime
command, or preparation for peacetime command).
 
> IMTU, a master\'s license is required to be a ship\'s captain.

See above for my suggestions on exceptions to this rule.

<<snip>>

