Frankie, the number of weapons deployed was definitely enough to wipe out
civilization as we know it. The US had at least one warhead per city of
50,000 persons in the Soviet Block (USSR & Warsaw Pact). The USSR had
enough warheads for stauration of the same. The total tonnage Per World
Capita was 2.5KT per person on the planet (assuming a planetary Pop of 5
Billion) [Time Magazine, 1990 or so, similar data published in Defense
Weekly in about 87] Since most (75%) of the worlds population lives in
concentrations where 2.5KT could easily wipe out more than 20 persons...

Add to that the non-nuclear armaments: Chem, Bio, and FAE, and the raw
destructive capacity that was DEPLOYED was Mutual Assured Destruction of
SOCIETIES. When you can drop a 0.5GT Warhead on EVERY production center in
the warsaw pact, and the Warsaw Pact can do the same to N. America and
Western Europe, that, as far as I am concerned, is enough to end the world
as we know it. And this doesn\'t count those 8" 2.5KT Artillery Nukes. I\'ve
read the US Army\'s FM on them (I know, I shouldn\'t have)... They were field
deployed.

Anyone who claims the Cold war was just a dream obviously slept through the
whole thing. I\'ve met far too many polish and russian ex-patriots, and too
many of my US fellow citizens, who\'ve lived in terror because they know
just how close nuclear war really came to being. People who are aware of
just how often DefCon 2 has been reached. People whose jobs have been to Be
Ready.

Ob Trav: There can be no comparable threat against the Imperium. Due to the
distances involved, and the scales of targets, any atrocities done will be
at worst a slow wave-front moving inward. Even the Star Trigger, if it
worked, is a marginally viable threat... you still have to deliver it.

