that make all our purported power look like a joke.  Several species
die-backs have occured throughout time.  The most notable being at the K-T
boundary.  Assuming the much-beloved "comet theory", you\'re talking energy
far in excess of what we can develop or deploy.  Ergo, I think the argument
that we can "destroy all life on Earth" is flawed.

>Add to that the non-nuclear armaments: Chem, Bio, and FAE, and the raw
