    'body' => 'On 26-11-99, Kyle Schuant said :

<<Snippage ocurred fore and aft>>

>You can\'t compare the explosion of lots of nukes with
>the explosion of a volcano. A volcano does not have a
>3million centigrade fireball, nor deadly radiation.
>Its blast is often supersonic, but it doesn\'t usually
>explode in the middle of a city (disaster movies
>notwithstanding). Also, one big bang doesn\'t make as
>much dust (for nuclear winters) as lots of "little"
>bangs. Lots of little ones cause more damage; this is
>the principle of the frag grenade.

Hmm, nice try, but wrong.  True, yer average volcanic eruption doesn\'t get
up to the temperatures found in nuclear detonation (which, BTW, only get to
a couple of thousand degrees Kelvin).  It does, however, emit large doses
of radiation, depending on eruption type.  Even better, it vents all sorts
of lovely gasses which if manufactured by man would be outlawed.  Rarely do
volcanoes in the middle of a city go off because humans are not so totally
moronic so as to build on the flanks of too many active hilltops.  When
they have, they\'ve discovered their mistake and not lived to tell of it.
Eruptions ala \'Volcano\' are historically rare.  However, can you say
Pompeii ?  It doesn\'t have to spew forth lava to be deadly.

As for spitting up ash, wrong again.  We find a fair few ash layers in
sedimentary rocks that must have been many, many metres thick when they
were laid.  Often, we find the same evidence from the same eruption
hundreds of kilometers from the eruption point itself.  One eruption in
recent history altered the climate across the globe.  Krakatua.  One single
eruption.  Heard as far away as Sydney in Australia where the Governor
thought Russian warships were bombarding his coastal defences.  Show me a
nuke that can do that !

ObTrav : Imagine a system where the populace of the mainworld is sitting on
the flanks of a volcano they think is extinct.  Say, Olympus Mons on Mars.
Big bugger.  What are they gonna do when it appears that it isn\'t extinct ?
 How do up and move millions of people, even in a high TL Third Imperium ?
Imagine the PC\'s fighting people off because they\'re the last ship out
after all the nobles\' yachts and Megacorps freighters have left.  Ooh,
that\'d be evil.

Dave
