	Not sure how such a statement could be made, but here\'s the numbers.
	At the height of the cold war, there were approximately 50,000
warheads in various stockpiles, averaging (WAG) probably less than 10
megatons.

	Now the damned statistics.  50,000 warheads x 10 megatons means, if
they were scattered perfectly in perfect conditions, they would effectively
destroy 25 mi^2 x 50,000 or 1.25 mio square miles.  Would this wipe out a
country the size of France?  I don\'t know the size of France, but California
