lithium-cobalt doped warhead could, over the span of a half-dozen years,
wipe out human and animal (and a sizeable fraction of vegetable) life on
this planet.  Leo Szilard pointed that out in what - 1957?  Basic physics
hasn\'t changed since then, and our understanding of the catastrophic
consequences of even small amounts of radiation in the natural environments
has only gotten better.

