    'body' => 'BTW, for those who were wondering about my statements about the Taupo
eruption, here\'s a reference:

http://www.gns.cri.nz/earthact/volcanoes/whitei.html#BACKGROUND ON THE TAUPO
VOLCANO

As you can see, the 181 AD eruption is estimated to have put around one
hundred cubic _kilometres_ of material into the atmosphere, and according to
other sources I\'ve read, several of those cubic kilometres were blown into
the stratosphere.

This is far more material than even a large number of nuclear explosions
could throw up. And it is the material in the stratosphere that will cause
any "nuclear winter" as the ash from firestorms and lower level injections
will fall to earth relatively quickly except in very unusual circumctances.

Think about this paragraph (taken from the above web site) for a bit :

"At the climax of this eruption, about 30km3 of pumice, ash and rock
fragments was erupted in only a few minutes and travelled horizontally as a
liquid flow, moving at speeds estimated at between 600-900kmh. It crossed
every obstacle in its path except the top of Mt Ruapehu."

(Mt. Ruapehu is another volcano nearby that got famous a year or so ago when
it\'s last eruption was put on the web, it\'s the second tallest mountain in
the North Island. )

Anther item I can\'t find a web reference to is the pyroclastic cloud (of
super-heated steam) from the 181AD explosion (that went out in front of the
above pumice/ash flow.) . There is evidence that this reached  reached the
Bombay hills some hundred miles or more from Taupo, killing (by scalding)
everything in that radius.

So you didn\'t have to worry about being boiled by the ash flow, you were
dead of the steam before you even heard the explosion.

What size nuke do you need to kill within minutes every exposed living thing
in a radius of one hundred miles ?

OB TRAV:
Just describe these events to your players as they lift-off, get them scared
as their ship barely outpaces the superheated steam and pumice flow.

And then, after they complain that this cannot be possible or natural, give
them the above reference.

Anyone interested in buying a fishing lodge on Lake Taupo ?

Frankie





Frankie
