Actually, that should be "solar flares IMPACTING THE EARTH\'S
MAGNETOSPHERE can and do generate EMP". Out in free space, all you have
to deal with is the trapped flux in the solar wind (much lower field
strengths) and the *huge* blast of high energy protons (think of it as
a badly out of focus CPAW beam). 

It\'s those protons crashing into the field lines and atmosphere near
the poles that cause the effects William describes. And it\'s the
similar (but more localized) particle fluxes from high altitude nukes
reacting with the magnetosphere that cause the widespread EMP. 

You will get *localized* EMP if you are close to *any* nuclear blast.
But you won\'t need to worry about it as you\'ll be well within the
lethal radius of the blast!

