Kenji, you\'ve been told wrong.  The convention in
Latin, followed today in other gendered romance
languages, is that, in general, if a plural inflected
word (typically noun, pronoun, adjective, or past
participle) refers to both men and women, the gender
of that word is masculine.  So Smith can have an
alumnae association, but Swarthmore must have an
