>legal on the world of origin?  If there is no formal Imperial regulation
>of such compounds, does the Imperium at least attempt to help worlds
>maintain their own regulations on importation of medicinal compounds?


I would suspect that the Imperium might have to involve itself in this sort
of scenario. Introduction of addictive drugs into a society can have grave
economic consequences. Even the distant Imperium doesn\'t want an industrial
world to be turned into a crack den. Historically, this tactic was used
deliberately by the British during the Opium Wars. On a smaller scale, the
introduction of alcohol to the American Indians was devastating.
