> better than the one I tried) help much with hayfever. For that 
> antihistamines or, more recently, steriods are the way to go.

Current evidence-based treatment for sinusitis :-
- - a non-sedating antihistamine (e.g. loratidine) ;
- - a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (e.g. paracetamol/acetaminophen
or ibuprofen) ; and
- - don\'t blow your nose - recent experiments suggest that this merely
inoculates the sinuses with the causative virii/whatever.
(You can generate pressures in excess of 200mmHg when nose-blowing ;
this is not to be sneezed or coughed at!).

Steroids for sinusitis are a bit of overkill, but they would work.

Acupuncture is good for migraines and tension headaches and some
analgesia, but there is no evidence of benefit for sinusitis.

Ditto for ascorbic acid.

Maintaining adequate hydration is a great general symptomatic relief
measure for a variety of problems.

Robert O\'Connor
Medico, Gamer
