    'file' => 'TML1999/TD991419.TXT',
    'subj' => 'Re: Different Technologies',
    'from' => 'tml@ksarul.com',
    'body' => 'One fundamental reason that everyone uses the same technology is that the
laws of physics are the same for all players.

Engineering is an exercise in constrained optimization, with the constraints
being physics, economics, etc, so the engineering solutions to problems will
be similar, given that the constraints are similar. It seems that economics
does not vary significantly across the Traveller universe, so with the same
laws of physics we should not be too surprised to find similar (note that I
said *similar* but not *identical*) technology.

We should expect to find greatly different man-machine interfaces, however,
since the interface will reflect a particular race\'s way of processing
sensory data and its general view of the world. Thus a human engineer may
find a Vargr manuever drive fairly incomprehensible even though it performs
the same basic functions as his more familliar systems.
