(enquiries to which are called PNC checks).  Within these  police
forces there are various specialised units  ...  Special  Branch,
T-Branch (anti-terrorist), the  Vice  Squad,  the  infamous  West
Midlands Serious Crime  squad,  the  Serious  Fraud  Office,  the
Complaints Investigation Branch, Criminal Investigation Division,
the Transport Police (for railways), etc.  In addition  there  is
Customs & Excise ... mostly visible at seaports and airports, but
able to pursue investigations anywhere in the  country.  Finally,
since the end (?) of the cold war MI5  (counterintelligence)  has
been trying to  gain  responsibility  for  counter-terrorism  and
anti-drugs (hoping to justify no  budget  cuts  for  itself).  In
general patrolling officers are unarmed.  Less well known is that
rail ticket inspectors (or the "Revenue Protection  Squad")  have
the powers to  formally  *arrest*  someone  travelling  by  train
without a valid ticket, although they usually just  give  out  an
on-the-spot fine.

IMTU I have different local police structures for each planet ...
with different rank titles.  A senior detective on one planet may
be a Constable, on another an Investigator,  on  yet  another  an
Arbiter, or even a Sherrif, and so on.  On some planets  suspects
are  considered  "innocent  until  proven  guilty",  others  have
innocent / guilty / not proven.  Basically,  no  standardisation.
Interstellar crimes fall under the jurisdiction of the  MOJ  (and
also the Imp Navy and IISS in the  case  of  piracy).  And  where
local criminals move to another planet the MOJ act like  INTERPOL
and coordinate different planet\'s local police forces.

Regards PLST
