    'date' => 'Wed, 1 Dec 1999 12:01:30  0800',
    'body' => 'The reason that you get the same solution for spaceflight is that your
constraints are the same. For power plants, coal is better if you have an
abundant supply of coal, nuclear is better if you don\'t have lots of
environmentalists (yes, that\'s a joke), etc. For spaceflight, you need lots
of power from a small power source. This will greatly limit your options for
power plant technology, for example. My rationalization for the same
technology everywhere is that the engineering challenges are similar enough
for all of the races to yield only one viable solution.

I think a good example is the construction of nuclear weapons. Imagine
different cultures developing nuclear weapons without the ability to spy on
their high-tech adversary (gratuitous bashing of defeated cold war
adversaries omitted with some difficulty). I will bet that the weapons will
be amazingly similar in construction. Same problem, same physics, same
solution.

