> vary significantly across the Traveller universe, so with the
> same laws of physics we should not be too surprised to find
> similar (note that I said *similar* but not *identical*)
> technology.

Two problems here:

- - First, the resource availability (mineral and otherwise) varies
  from planet to planet which will affect the economics of  using
  different technologies.  (eg. A lack of local radioactivies may
  mean  fission  reactors  are  economically  unviable,   leading
  instead to a dependance on solar power, etc.)

- - Second, for isolated worlds (outside the 3I or similar)  it  is
  possible to progress to medium TL without fully  exploring  all
  technologies technically feasable to low TL.  (eg. Romans  with
  SMGs)

Okay, high TL multi-world empires would move  towards  technology
homogeny so the 3I and Zhos whould be similar, but below that ...

Regards PLST
