    'topic' => ' Different Technologies',
    'body' => 'From: Bob Sanders <bsanders@amghome.com>


> Reading the ship designs using solar sails, and looking at FF&S, Gurps,
etc.
> I have some questions that has always bothered me about Traveller, and
would
> like to get some ideas from the crowd.  Why is it that every race in the
> Traveller universe uses the same technology?

It\'s mainly because the wonder technologies of Traveller (contra-gravity,
reactionless thrusters and small fusion power plants specifically) eliminate
any and all competition. They are also cheap enough to be really pervasive
in the Third Imperium setting.

Personally, I\'m in the same boat as you. It becomes a real problem when
you\'re designing ships and vehicles because there\'s no reason not to use
those technologies. As a result, two ships of the exact same size built by
different cultures will tend to be, at least functionally, *exactly* the
same. That may work for other people, but it doesn\'t for me. What\'s the
point of visiting strange new worlds and civilizations if they\'re all going
to be exactly the same?
