    'index' => 'ef470',
    'topic' => ' Different Technologies',
    'body' => '"Bob Sanders" <bsanders@amghome.com> wrote:

>I agree, but we also know that many roads can get you to the same
>destination.  ForEx. look at the many different types of power generation
>plants in the world.  Gas, coal, nuke, solar, wind, etc... they are all
>optimized (the best they can be at existing technology) for their function.
>However they all still provide power.  That doesn\'t answer my question of
>how the different races all developed the same solution to the engineering
>problem produced by space travel.

The problem is that Fusion is simply better than any sort of power
generation system which does not involve antimatter or other highly
exotic, *very* high TL solutions.  Fusion power uses easily available fuel
(hydrogen) and generates a huge amount of power for a small amount of fuel
(and in a relatively small space in Traveller). Nothing else works nearly
as well. 

The case for Thrusters is even better.  Fission drives, solar sails, and
most other solutions are honestly fairly pitiful for getting around a
solar system in anything resembling a reasonable amount of time. 

Fusion rockets & Heplar both work OK, but are incredibly inferior to
Thrusters, since they require considerable amounts of fuel or reaction
mass and thrusters do not.  Thrusters are the only way you can do 1 G
continuous thrust boosts from one planet to another.  With that sort of
advantage everyone who came across such things would drop their existing
technologies and adopt thrusters as soon as they could buy or duplicate
them. 

Some technologies are simply better.


