Here\'s the only problem with your analysis, and why I didn\'t go this route.

Armor and framework don\'t have any volume in GURPS Vehicles. This is an
abstraction, to avoid iterative volume calculations. It works okay for
hulls that are thin relative to their volume, but it breaks down pretty
rapidly if you push it too far.

In this case, you have to consider the volume of all that steel. Say that
steel has a density of 8 g/cc (I don\'t have CRC to consult, so don\'t take
this literally). Your armor and framework together would take up 35 cf, on
top of the 6 cf of contents -- which throws off your drag and airspeed
calculations, and prevents the missile from using standard launchers.
