> disjointed at the time.  A couple of centuries later, OTOH, the
> transition will appear to have been much smoother.

It depends on how tech level is defined. With the appearance of certain
technologies (such as the computer, jump drive, contra-gravity and
reactionless thrusters) the transition will not only appear "disjointed" it
will actually *be* disjointed.
