> Well, *obviously*, because you can 1) make money and 2) kill them.  What
> other reason, *realistically*, do you think people *rationally* need?

IMHO, you missed at least two other reasons for "visiting strange new
worlds":

1.  Simple curiosity.  Terran monkeyboys will often travel to unusual
places just to see what\'s there.  Charles Darwin\'s voyage aboard HMS
BEAGLE is a pretty good example of this motive.

2.  "Been There, Done That":  An even more potent motive for human
exploration has been the desire to be the first to visit some place. 
Sir Edmund Hillary [Mt. Everest], Admiral Byrd [the North Pole], and
Neil Armstrong [Earth\'s Moon] are all good examples of this motive.

Neither of the motives which I have mentioned directly involve wealth or
conquest.  They are, nonetheless, powerful reasons for human exploration
to date.

