    'index' => 'ef518',
    'month' => '12',
    'body' => 'In mail you write:

> Reading the ship designs using solar sails, and looking at FF&S, Gurps, etc.
> I have some questions that has always bothered me about Traveller, and would
> like to get some ideas from the crowd.  Why is it that every race in the
> Traveller universe uses the same technology?  Jump drives I can understand,
> put power plants, maneuver drives, hulls, computers, weapons, etc, could and
> should be different.  And if they are different (thus adding much to the
> alien flavor to the game) what would each race be likely to use?

Well, the trick is that everybody is dealing with the *same* universe.
So the "best" way of doing something is the same for everyone. Chinese
"junks" are *very* different than Western multi-masted ships in
construction. Yet they are bother sailing ships and operate much the
same. 

> Imps: basic stuff
> Droyn: sails, solar collectors, geneered brains?
> Aslan: fusion drives?
> Hivers: Grown ships (like the pentapods (sp) from T2300)
> Others?
>
> I see that each would/could have different strengths & weaknesses, and that
> all uses of technology could be found through out known space.

Like I said, if any of these are more efficient than what the others
use, then it won\'t be all *that* long before the others switch to it.

The only exceptions will be cases were a race can\'t *physically*
tolerate something about the drive/device. 

And the rare cases where there\'s a social "taboo", such as Imperials
using psi. So you might be able to have a race using "grown" ships
because it\'s against their principles to travel via machine. 

